"a.[生]冷血的；残酷的 【英】 adj. (生)冷血的; 残酷的(without pity) 【例】 a cold-blooded murderer adj. 无情的; 残酷的; 冷血的 【例】Snakes are cold-blooded 蛇是冷血动物. I am a cold-blooded killer 我是一个冷血杀手 【记】cold 冷 blooded 血 cold-blooded (adj.)  also cold blooded; 1590s, of persons, ""without emotion, unfeeling;"" of actions, from 1828. The phrase refers to the old notion that blood temperature rose with excitement. In the literal sense, of reptiles, etc., from c.1600. From cold (adj.) + blood (n.). Related: Cold-bloodedly; cold-bloodedness."
